# Release-export hygiene.
#
# Exclude maintainer working-state from `git archive` exports / release
# tarballs so the distributed artefact is fork-clean. `.working/` holds
# per-run QA records, session handoffs, metrics, decisions, and the
# detailed-CHANGELOG mirror (the maintainer's audit trail); an adopter needs
# none of it.
#
# Scope note: `export-ignore` affects `git archive` only. A `git clone` still
# includes `.working/` and full git history; true clone/history cleanliness is
# a separate history-rewrite step. Adopters may also simply delete `.working/`
# after cloning (the fork convention documented in the root CHANGELOG preamble
# and the change-tracking governance rule).
.working/ export-ignore
